flowRoot.flowPara: Our project website and documentation can be found at www.openstreetmap.org. Signing up is quick, easy, and of course, free of charge.
We also have a wiki with a wealth of project information, topic- and country-specific mailing lists, and a Q&A help system if you get stuck.

The map above shows an OpenStreetMap rendering of London. Just like the map on the other side and the globe on the front page, it was created with Open Source software. Many Open Source software projects have been created specially for OpenStreetMap.

OpenStreetMap data is published under the "Open Database License 1.0" (ODbL). Anyone can share, adapt, and create works from our data freely, provided that they give attribution to "OpenStreetMap contributors", and share any adapted databases under the same license.
